result.execSummary:
The defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Misdemeanor Theft, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: (see plea hearing docket event for waiver)

(Case called at 1:00 PM)
Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell in court with Attorney Robert Allen Thorson.  Attorney Tiffany Winter in court for State of Wisconsin. 
State in compliance with victim notification requirements.  State outlines the agreement for the Court.  Defense requests that the cash bond be refunded to the poster - Court orders the $500 cash bond be applied to the restitution amount only and the remainder be returned to the poster.  Defendant advised of her right to preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing- waiver accepted by Court.  Defendant acknowledges Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form.  Defendant advised of elements and maximum possible penalties of the offenses to which she will plead.  Court finds Defendant guilty based on pleas of No Contest to Count 1: Felony Bail Jumping (WITHOUT Repeater), Count 4: Possession of Narcotic Drugs (WITHOUT enhancers), Count 5: Possession of Methamphetamine (WITHOUT Repeater), and Count 6: Misdemeanor Theft (WITHOUT Repeater).  Any other charges are dismissed and read in.  Defendant makes a statement.  
Court withholds sentence and orders 3 years of probation on Counts 1, 4, and 5; 1 year probation on Count 6, all with the following conditions: 9 months in jail, with Huber (on Count 4) all stayed for use by the treatment court team.  Comply with and successfully complete treatment court program.  Undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  No alcohol, no entry into any bars, taverns, or liquor stores.  No use or possession of any illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  No contact with Stone Countertop Outlet or its employees.  No contact with S.S. No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting.  Restitution in the amount of $200 + 10% surcharge, joint and several with S.S.  Comply with any conditions/programming per agent.  121 days sentence credit if revoked from probation.
Waiver of Prelim on October 24, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
